The paper deals with compressed sensing (CS) with prior information, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several sub-fields of CS. The most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory), which deals with the fundamental limits of data compression and transmission. The paper proposes a new approach to integrate prior information into CS, which involves maximizing the correlation between the prior knowledge and the desired signal. This approach is based on the idea of exploiting the statistical structure of the signal, which is a common theme in cs.SP (Signal Processing) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also presents a geometric analysis of the proposed method under sub-Gaussian measurements, which is related to cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.MM (Multimedia). Overall, the paper covers a broad range of topics in CS, but the emphasis on information theory and signal processing makes cs.IT and cs.SP the most likely categories.
